originalText.text: Do not go here. This old lady will take your clothes out before they are done. She advocates for her friends and neighbors but mistreats anyone else that's foreign to her. I've been here 3 times and each time she has treated me with such disrespect. It's not worth your money or time to be disrespected by an aged woman stuck in her ways. May her laundromat go down with her nasty attitude. Do not go here.

originalText.text: Unlike other laundromats nearby, this one uses a card system: it's $5 to get a card, you can only load it with cash AND the machine won't take anything smaller than a $5 bill. There's nowhere to sit, and way more washers than dryers so stuff takes forever to dry - and when it is finally done, there's no space to fold anything. Everyone who works there seemed nice but if you don't speak Spanish, it can be very hard to communicate any problems with a machine or the card system.

originalText.text: Horrible place, save your money and walk a little further somewhere else. Not only are the machines old, but they barely work. If you wash or dry your clothes and are not there waiting the second it's done, the employees will grab it and put it in the basket. Not even the other customers will do that. I have lost multiple socks and underwear due to them doing this.

originalText.text: My fiancé and I recently moved in the area and this is where I come to do our laundry now. The ladies that work here in the morning and super cool, very sweet. But the evening lady?? Oh God. I stopped going during the night time just to avoid seeing her. She has the nastiest attitude! Like she is mad at the world. She is nice with certain people but she will move your things without asking, slam carts near your seat, never holds the door for you even if she sees you struggling. They have “reserved dryers” since they have a drop off service and there are times that she won’t use it for over half hour and she’ll see you waiting for one when they’re all taken and she won’t let you use it even if you ask nicely; which I don’t get because she looks like she’s mad at everything, so you would think she’d want you gone faster. Her aura is just so negative it’s disgusting.

originalText.text: The women in charge; whether it be in the morning or afternoon, both are them have very nasty attitudes. They move around your personal carts without any hesitation, no asking permission or excuse me. They see you struggle to open the door and just watch. The cards are $5 just to put more money to wash the clothes. It’s ridiculous in there. Not recommending ANYONE to go there.
